> what you want (if you has been testing features that are in the devel
> branch but need to correct a bug on release).  Sometimes it's better to
> checkout the release branch:
>
> git checkout -b <RELEASE_X_Y> upstream/<RELEASE_X_Y>
>
> git pull
>
>
> but then individually modify and commit changes like you did for the other
> branch.
